---
import SectionLabel from "../../elements/SectionLabel.astro";
import Heading from "../../elements/Heading.astro";
import BodyText from "../../elements/BodyText.astro";
---

<section
  class="bg-rh-warm-light dark:bg-rh-warm-dark py-28 md:py-40 px-6 md:px-10"
  id="override-section"
>
  <div class="mx-auto w-full max-w-[1400px]">
    <!-- Terminal Header -->
    <div class="override-reveal mb-10">
      <SectionLabel text="> SYS.OVERRIDE // SOLUTION_IDENTIFIED" />
    </div>

    <!-- Headline -->
    <Heading class="override-reveal mb-16 max-w-5xl tracking-tight">
      The answer isn't more tools.
      <span class="text-rh-ember">It's architecture.</span>
    </Heading>

    <!-- Two-column: What it's not / What it is -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 lg:gap-16">
      <!-- Left column: The problem -->
      <div>
        <div class="override-reveal mb-10">
          <BodyText class="mb-6">
            The organizations that survived each transition weren't the ones with
            the best technology. They were the ones that redesigned how their people
            connect, coordinate, and stay.
          </BodyText>
        </div>

        <div class="override-reveal">
          <p
            class="font-mono text-sm md:text-base text-rh-ink/40 dark:text-rh-chalk/40 leading-relaxed"
          >
            <span class="line-through">That's not culture consulting.</span><br />
            <span class="line-through">Not community management.</span><br />
            <span class="line-through">Not marketing.</span>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Right column: The answer -->
      <div>
        <div class="override-reveal mb-10">
          <p
            class="text-lg md:text-xl text-rh-ink dark:text-rh-chalk leading-relaxed mb-6"
          >
            It's <strong class="font-bold text-rh-ember">Human Architecture</strong>.
            The intentional design of how people find you, connect to each other,
            stay, and build together.
          </p>
          <BodyText>
            It's the operating system underneath your culture, your community, your
            visibility, and your retention. Most organizations have never
            intentionally designed this. They inherited it. Bolted on tools.
            Wondered why nothing holds.
          </BodyText>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- The closer -->
    <div class="override-reveal mt-16">
      <p
        class="font-heading text-3xl md:text-5xl font-black uppercase italic text-rh-ink dark:text-rh-chalk leading-tight"
      >
        Almost nobody is building it.
      </p>
      <p
        class="font-heading text-3xl md:text-5xl font-black uppercase italic text-rh-ember leading-tight mt-4"
      >
        We are.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<script>
  import { gsap } from "gsap";
  import { ScrollTrigger } from "gsap/ScrollTrigger";
  gsap.registerPlugin(ScrollTrigger);

  gsap.fromTo(
    ".override-reveal",
    { opacity: 0, y: 50 },
    {
      opacity: 1,
      y: 0,
      duration: 1,
      stagger: 0.3,
      ease: "power3.out",
      scrollTrigger: {
        trigger: "#override-section",
        start: "top 70%",
      },
    },
  );
</script>
